## Notes

- 8 kyu lean heavily on built-in methods (`.split`, `.reverse`, `.join`, `.filter`).
- 7 kyu mixes array + string work; this is where `map`/`filter`/`reduce` really click.
- 6 kyu introduces object/hash-map thinking — frequency counters, lookups, grouping. Pure "object" katas at the easier levels are rare on Codewars; the natural way to practice objects is via these counting/grouping problems.
- If a link 404s, search the kata name directly on <https://www.codewars.com/kata/search/> — slug formats occasionally change.
